"         warlock\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/spellcasting/spells/counterspell.md:10
msgid "# Counterspell _3rd-level abjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/spellcasting/spells/counterspell.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 reaction, which you take when you see a creature within "
"60 feet of you casting a spell    \n"
"**Range:** 60 feet    \n"
"**Components:** S    \n"
"**Duration:** Instantaneous \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/spellcasting/spells/counterspell.md:17
msgid ""
"You attempt to interrupt a creature in the process of casting a spell. If "
"the creature is casting a spell of 3rd level or lower, its spell fails and "
"has no effect. If it is casting a spell of 4th level or higher, make an "
"ability check using your spellcasting ability. The DC equals 10 + the "
"spell's level. On a success, the creature's spell fails and has no effect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/spellcasting/spells/counterspell.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th "
"level or higher, the interrupted spell has no effect if its level is less "
"than or equal to the level of the spell slot you used.\n"
msgstr ""
